Inventory setup will vary greatly depending on your gear and team. When deciding what supplies to bring, keep in mind that Spindel frequently drops large quantities of un-noted blighted food or potions that replace supplies used during the fight. Make sure to have the following:
* [[Grey chinchompa]]s, [[dart]]s/[[throwing knife|throwing knives]], or [[blighted ancient ice sack]]s for killing the spiderlings quickly, ordered from fastest to slowest
* [[Looting bag]]
* [[Stamina potion]]
* ([[Divine super combat potion|Divine]]) [[super combat potion]]
* [[Anti-venom]]/[[Sanfew serum]](s) — cures/prevents venom from player killers.
* [[Blighted super restore]]s
* [[Blighted manta ray]] or [[blighted anglerfish]] (if the player is 93 or higher hitpoints) for the rest, and multiple [[blighted karambwan]]
Optional:
* [[Phoenix necklace]] — emergency healing whilst tanking
* [[Saradomin brew]]s — more expensive outlast healing, combo eating with hard food is invaluable
* [[Royal seed pod]] — if not bringing a charged [[amulet of glory]] or [[ring of wealth]]
* [[Games necklace]] or [[revenant cave teleport]] to reach the [[Web Chasm]] faster.
* [[Blighted vengeance sack]]s, [[runes]] for [[Vengeance]], or for [[thralls]] and/or [[Death Charge]]
** Death charge can be cast off cooldown with frequent spiderling spawns.
* [[Divine rune pouch]] locked with a trouver parchment — if using Arceeus spellbook, allows for more supplies.
